  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Programme Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Plan, organise, implement, monitor and evaluate programmes and activities to address residents’ psychosocial needs.</li><li>Actively engage with community groups and volunteers to promote involvement in organising and implementation of\nprogrammes and activities to residents and clients.</li><li>Builds and maintains good interpersonal relations with all colleagues, residents and public.</li><li>Prepare materials for conducting of recreational programme and events.</li><li>Coordinate transport, volunteers and staff to ensure logistical requirements for safe and efficient delivery of programmes are met.</li><li>Ensure safety of residents during therapy sessions, activities and outings at all times.</li><li>Guide, supervise and train caregivers & volunteers on their performance of duties and implementation of activities for the residents.</li><li>Comply with policy and procedures, clinical standards, operational KPIs and service qualities of the Home.</li><li>Ensure all equipment and activity tools are in good condition and working order. </li><li>Keep proper inventory and maintain all activity equipment and fixtures by regular servicing and replacement of equipment.</li></ul><p>Requirement:</p><ul><li>Diploma or equivalent in any discipline</li><li>At least two years of working experience in a similar position in a Nursing Home</li><li>Able to converse in local dialect</li><li>Passionate in serving the needy and vulnerable elderly</li><li>Have a listening and coaching skills</li><li>Able to work independently</li></ul><p><strong>Competency:</strong></p><p>Must-Have:</p><ul><li>Collaborative Practices Across Disciplines and Sectors – Level 2  </li><li>Social Service Programme Development – Level 2  </li><li>Social Service Programme Evaluation – Level 2  </li><li>Social Service Programme Implementation – Level 2  </li><li>Stakeholder Management – Level 2  </li><li>Trends Evaluation and Application – Level 2  </li><li>Diversity Awareness and Management – Level 2  </li></ul><p>Critical Core Skills:</p><ul><li>Communication - Intermediate </li><li>Influence - Basic </li><li>Collaboration - Intermediate</li><li>Adaptability - Basic</li><li>Decision Making – Intermediate </li></ul><p>*Please refer to Technical Skills and Competency (TSCs) and Critical Core Skills (CCSs) in Skills Framework for Social Service Industry via this link <a href=\"https://www.skillsfuture.gov.sg/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">SSG | Social Service (skillsfuture.gov.sg)</a>  </p>",
